The Plateau State gubernatorial aspirants on the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC) have threatened to dump the party if due process is not followed in electing the partyâ€™s flag bearer ahead of the primaries billed for May 31 in the state. Addressing a press conference in Jos on Monday, Chairman/convener of the forum Plateau APC Governorship aspirants, Chief Amon Gizo warned that an attempt by the Governor of Plateau State, Simon Lalong or the party hierarchy to foist a candidate on the party and the people of plateau state will be resisted. According to Chief Gizo, the forum is also asking the party leadership to address forthwith the use of ad hoc delegates with amendments for the primaries. -Advertisement- He added that the list of those who are members of the forum includes the Deputy Governor, Sonnie Tyoden, Professor Dakas Dakas, Mr Sunday Biggs, Doctor Patrick Dakum and 14 others, adding that aspirants are also demanding that there should be no imposition of any kind and consensus should be done by the aspirants themselves. He added that any aspirant that emerged through consensus will be supported by the rest of the aspirants and be given the blueprints of other aspirants to be embedded into his manifesto and programs. They queried the body language of Governor Lalong as his family, wife and in-laws are doing everything to impose a candidate on the party among several issues raised.